WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.635 --> 00:00:03.365
I'll raise.

2
00:00:03.437 --> 00:00:05.872
I've got a good
feeling about this hand.

3
00:00:07.641 --> 00:00:09.701
Too rich for me. Fold.

4
00:00:11.678 --> 00:00:14.944
Big surprise. rookie.
That's all you ever do is fold.

5
00:00:15.816 --> 00:00:18.581
Call. What do you
say to that. big shot?

6
00:00:22.289 --> 00:00:24.690
I say...

7
00:00:28.962 --> 00:00:31.761
The last card didn't
make Mr. O'Grady's flush.

8
00:00:33.300 --> 00:00:36.759
Mr. Duritz was smart to fold
'cause he missed his straight.

9
00:00:42.576 --> 00:00:46.707
And you. Mr. Hastings.
your cards just stink.

10
00:00:47.180 --> 00:00:49.672
You're bluffing. I call.

11
00:00:51.785 --> 00:00:54.516
Two pair. Jacks
and 7s. Oh! Damn it!

12
00:00:54.588 --> 00:00:56.056
Every time.

13
00:00:56.123 --> 00:00:57.333
You'd think we'd
know better by now.

14
00:00:57.357 --> 00:00:59.622
What the hell is goin' on here?

15
00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:05.430
Poker. Shawn? Poker?

16
00:01:05.699 --> 00:01:07.327
What were you thinking?

17
00:01:07.801 --> 00:01:09.702
I don't know. I
get bored waiting.

18
00:01:09.770 --> 00:01:11.363
Oh. well. why didn't
you just say so?

19
00:01:11.438 --> 00:01:13.737
I mean. if you're
bored. I guess it's okay.

20
00:01:13.807 --> 00:01:15.708
What is wrong with you?

21
00:01:15.776 --> 00:01:18.075
How do you even
know how to play poker?

22
00:01:18.211 --> 00:01:19.611
Mr. Hastings taught me.

23
00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:21.148
Hastings. uh?

24
00:01:21.248 --> 00:01:23.080
Well. I want it to stop.
Do you understand?

25
00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:24.994
No more poker. no more
gambling. You're too young.

26
00:01:25.018 --> 00:01:26.884
Dad. I don't gamble. I win.

27
00:01:26.954 --> 00:01:28.980
You win? Oh. uh-huh.

28
00:01:29.056 --> 00:01:30.922
And approximately
how often do you lose?

29
00:01:30.991 --> 00:01:32.755
I don't know. You don't know.

30
00:01:32.826 --> 00:01:34.454
Well. I haven't lost yet.

31
00:01:36.496 --> 00:01:38.488
How much? How much did you win?

32
00:01:45.839 --> 00:01:47.000
Is that it?

33
00:01:53.046 --> 00:01:55.311
All right. son. listen to me.

34
00:01:56.149 --> 00:01:57.947
Just because you
can do something

35
00:01:58.018 --> 00:01:59.680
doesn't always mean
that you should do it.

36
00:01:59.753 --> 00:02:01.030
do you understand
what I'm saying?

37
00:02:01.054 --> 00:02:02.113
No.

38
00:02:03.890 --> 00:02:05.153
Hey. that's mine!

39
00:02:05.225 --> 00:02:06.225
Not anymore.

40
00:02:06.293 --> 00:02:07.317
Yes. it is!

41
00:02:07.394 --> 00:02:09.659
Uh-uh. no. No. no. no.
no. I'm giving it away.

42
00:02:09.730 --> 00:02:11.528
Giving it away.
Why? Because I can.

43
00:02:11.598 --> 00:02:14.397
And according to your little
philosophy. your poker philosophy.

44
00:02:14.468 --> 00:02:16.937
if I can. then I should. right?

45
00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:25.044
I know it might seem like you're
gonna win every time. Shawn.

46
00:02:25.112 --> 00:02:26.705
but no matter how good you are.

47
00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:28.715
there's always
somebody who's better.

48
00:02:29.049 --> 00:02:31.211
And there's one
rule in gambling.

49
00:02:31.418 --> 00:02:34.013
the house always
wins. Eventually.

50
00:02:35.656 --> 00:02:37.625
Do you understand
what I'm saying?

51
00:02:37.691 --> 00:02:38.886
Don't gamble.

52
00:02:38.959 --> 00:02:40.291
Not for money.

53
00:02:40.861 --> 00:02:43.021
I got 10 bucks says you
can't make this shot. Ooh!

54
00:02:44.197 --> 00:02:46.325
Gus. I can't take your money.

55
00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:48.626
That's right. 'Cause
you can't make the shot.

56
00:02:48.702 --> 00:02:50.000
I could easily make the shot.

57
00:02:50.070 --> 00:02:53.063
which is why I can't take your
money. There's no sport in it.

58
00:02:53.373 --> 00:02:55.069
I say you're all mouth.

59
00:02:55.142 --> 00:02:56.838
I'm all mouth? Yep.

60
00:02:57.711 --> 00:02:58.770
All right.

61
00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:06.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

62
00:03:11.892 --> 00:03:13.622
Sail straight. my precious.

63
00:03:21.568 --> 00:03:23.503
Okay. Double or nothing.

64
00:03:23.570 --> 00:03:25.163
Trivia question
this time. History.

65
00:03:25.238 --> 00:03:26.900
Grover Cleveland. Damn!

66
00:03:26.973 --> 00:03:29.340
How do you do that?
It's the sweetness.

67
00:03:29.643 --> 00:03:32.203
So. this is how you
spend your days.

68
00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:34.771
Oh. my God! Dad.
what are you doing here?

69
00:03:34.848 --> 00:03:37.909
Nice. Is that the way you greet all the
people that come through your door?

70
00:03:37.984 --> 00:03:39.509
That's exactly how
I greet everyone.

71
00:03:39.586 --> 00:03:41.452
Maybe that's why
business is down. Hmm.

72
00:03:41.521 --> 00:03:42.784
Are you gonna invite me in?

73
00:03:42.856 --> 00:03:44.256
Oh. yeah. please... No!

74
00:03:44.324 --> 00:03:45.587
This could be a trick.

75
00:03:45.659 --> 00:03:48.171
What's the rule with vampires.
don't they have to be invited in?

76
00:03:48.195 --> 00:03:49.372
What are you
talking about. Shawn?

77
00:03:49.396 --> 00:03:52.332
Gus. you've seen <i>Lost Boys</i>
14 times. What's the rule?

78
00:03:52.466 --> 00:03:53.934
You're on your own.

79
00:03:56.870 --> 00:03:58.532
Is this all there is?

80
00:03:58.739 --> 00:04:01.709
Actually. this is the.
uh. satellite office.

81
00:04:01.775 --> 00:04:04.609
Main headquarters is in
an underground ice cave

82
00:04:04.678 --> 00:04:06.909
Gus and I sculpted last winter.

83
00:04:06.980 --> 00:04:08.278
What about your license?

84
00:04:08.348 --> 00:04:11.284
Ahem. my pilot's license?
It's out back in the Cessna.

85
00:04:11.351 --> 00:04:14.321
Or perhaps you're
referring to my license to kill.

86
00:04:14.387 --> 00:04:16.413
Revoked. Problems at
the Kazakhstan border.

87
00:04:16.490 --> 00:04:18.468
I could give you the details.
but then I'd have to kill you.

88
00:04:18.492 --> 00:04:21.326
which I can't do because my
license to kill has been revoked.

89
00:04:21.394 --> 00:04:24.057
I'm talkin' about your
private eye license.

90
00:04:24.164 --> 00:04:26.258
Well. you need one. don't ya?

91
00:04:26.333 --> 00:04:28.359
Psychics are exempt
from the requirements.

92
00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:31.564
Oh. well. hurray for loopholes!

93
00:04:34.007 --> 00:04:35.669
A little dark.

94
00:04:35.742 --> 00:04:39.008
Probably could use a couple more lamps.
you know. probably killing your eyes.

95
00:04:39.079 --> 00:04:42.481
That outlet... Ah. yeah.
looks a little overloaded.

96
00:04:42.549 --> 00:04:45.661
Yeah. I think that plasma. you'd probably
do better by puttin' it on that wall.

97
00:04:45.685 --> 00:04:48.365
you'd have less glare comin' in
through the window in the afternoon.

98
00:04:48.421 --> 00:04:50.500
You know what. Dad. I really
appreciate you makin' the long drive down

99
00:04:50.524 --> 00:04:51.601
and Feng Shui
it up sweet for us.

100
00:04:51.625 --> 00:04:52.902
but we're kind of in the
middle of something here.

101
00:04:52.926 --> 00:04:55.691
What would that be.
Shawn? Would that be NBA

102
00:04:55.962 --> 00:04:59.626
garbage can hoops. or
trivia super challenge?

103
00:04:59.699 --> 00:05:01.429
Believe it or not.
we have an 11:00.

104
00:05:01.501 --> 00:05:03.299
So maybe we should wrap this up.

105
00:05:03.370 --> 00:05:05.965
Yeah. it's a little too
late for that. Shawn.

106
00:05:10.277 --> 00:05:12.109
I am your 11:00.

107
00:05:18.018 --> 00:05:21.455
<i>I know. you know That
I'm not telling the truth</i>

108
00:05:21.521 --> 00:05:24.548
<i>I know. you know They
just don't have any proof</i>

109
00:05:24.624 --> 00:05:27.753
<i>Embrace the deception
Learn how to bend</i>

110
00:05:27.928 --> 00:05:32.195
<i>Your worst inhibitions tend
to psych you out in the end</i>

111
00:05:38.505 --> 00:05:41.475
Bill Peterson. He
owns Peterson Motors.

112
00:05:41.575 --> 00:05:43.786
Met him about 20 years ago
when I grabbed a couple of punks

113
00:05:43.810 --> 00:05:45.369
boosting tires off of his lot.

114
00:05:45.445 --> 00:05:47.223
Shawn. shouldn't you be
writing some of this down?

115
00:05:47.247 --> 00:05:49.182
Why would I do that?
Will there be a quiz?

116
00:05:49.249 --> 00:05:51.150
Just shut up and pay attention.

117
00:05:51.218 --> 00:05:53.813
I got a call from him yesterday.
He's got a kid. Brandon.

118
00:05:53.887 --> 00:05:55.879
He's just a little
younger than you.

119
00:05:55.956 --> 00:05:57.834
He thinks his son might
be mixed up in something.

120
00:05:57.858 --> 00:05:59.669
Like what? Well. he'll fill
you in when he gets here.

121
00:05:59.693 --> 00:06:02.238
The point is. he doesn't want the
cops involved. So. he called me.

122
00:06:02.262 --> 00:06:04.822
And you said...
I said I'm retired

123
00:06:04.898 --> 00:06:06.538
and he should definitely
involve the cops.

124
00:06:06.600 --> 00:06:09.434
Sweet. You came all the way
down here to tell us that. Awesome.

125
00:06:09.502 --> 00:06:11.869
No. Shawn. He doesn't
want his son in trouble.

126
00:06:11.938 --> 00:06:15.773
and I might have mentioned to
Peterson accidentally that. you. uh...

127
00:06:16.643 --> 00:06:18.305
You might be able to help.

128
00:06:18.378 --> 00:06:21.576
Whoa. time out! Flag on the
play! Did you vouch for me?

129
00:06:21.648 --> 00:06:23.742
No. I wouldn't say I
exactly vouched for you.

130
00:06:23.817 --> 00:06:25.843
Gus. Henry vouched for
me. I did not vouch for you!

131
00:06:25.919 --> 00:06:28.616
You were bragging on me.
You have a dad-crush on me.

132
00:06:28.688 --> 00:06:30.122
Shawn. I was not
bragging on you.

133
00:06:30.190 --> 00:06:34.457
I merely restated stats about your
track record that are in the newspaper.

134
00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:36.120
Let's hug it out.
Put your arms down.

135
00:06:36.196 --> 00:06:37.740
Gimme a hug. Put your...
No. I'm not gonna give you...

136
00:06:37.764 --> 00:06:40.256
If I'd known that Peterson
was gonna insist on hiring you.

137
00:06:40.333 --> 00:06:41.911
I would've blasted
your character outright

138
00:06:41.935 --> 00:06:44.962
and I would've mentioned your
unnatural fear of pointy things.

139
00:06:45.038 --> 00:06:47.007
Ah! Distaste for pointy things.

140
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:48.837
Please. just do
me this one favor.

141
00:06:48.909 --> 00:06:51.504
Would you listen to the man's
story. tell him you can't help?

142
00:06:51.578 --> 00:06:53.444
Send him to the cops.
and whatever you do.

143
00:06:53.513 --> 00:06:56.677
don't do it with all that
rolling your eyes around

144
00:06:56.750 --> 00:06:59.345
and all that floppy crap.

145
00:06:59.419 --> 00:07:00.478
What is this?

146
00:07:00.553 --> 00:07:02.715
First of all. I don't flop
around all the time. okay?

147
00:07:02.789 --> 00:07:04.724
My game is
predicated on finesse.

148
00:07:04.791 --> 00:07:06.636
How dare you criticize my
job? He's here. he's here.

149
00:07:06.660 --> 00:07:07.837
Okay. don't tell him I came by.

150
00:07:07.861 --> 00:07:10.228
You got a back way out of
this place? You came through it.

151
00:07:10.297 --> 00:07:11.321
Oh. right.

152
00:07:17.137 --> 00:07:18.264
Excuse me. you Shawn?

153
00:07:18.338 --> 00:07:20.773
Yes. that's correct.
Mr. Peterson.

154
00:07:23.043 --> 00:07:24.807
Wow. that is my name.

155
00:07:24.878 --> 00:07:26.779
Don't be too impressed. Bill.

156
00:07:26.846 --> 00:07:28.646
I could have gotten that
information anywhere.

157
00:07:28.715 --> 00:07:31.014
After all. Peterson
Motors is gigantic.

158
00:07:31.117 --> 00:07:33.086
Yeah. well. I'm
suitably impressed.

159
00:07:33.153 --> 00:07:34.815
Don't be. Burton Guster.

160
00:07:34.888 --> 00:07:36.117
Pleasure to meet you.

161
00:07:36.189 --> 00:07:38.590
Look. I'll get right to it.
I have a son. Brandon.

162
00:07:38.658 --> 00:07:41.355
Up until a few weeks ago. he
worked for me. Now he's disappeared.

163
00:07:41.428 --> 00:07:43.761
What happened a few
weeks ago? I fired him.

164
00:07:43.863 --> 00:07:45.456
He was lazy. directionless.

165
00:07:45.532 --> 00:07:48.331
I thought I could get him to
buckle down. focus in on something.

166
00:07:48.401 --> 00:07:49.596
How did that go?

167
00:07:49.669 --> 00:07:52.833
Well. he's been evicted from his
apartment. his cell phone's been cut off

168
00:07:52.906 --> 00:07:56.843
and he forged a check from my
account to the tune of $30.000.

169
00:07:57.978 --> 00:08:00.277
I need to find my
son. Can you help me?

170
00:08:00.347 --> 00:08:02.491
Well. Mr. Peterson. this
sounds like a case for the police.

171
00:08:02.515 --> 00:08:03.574
Let me get you a number.

172
00:08:03.650 --> 00:08:05.642
Gus. don't be a gooey
chocolate chip cookie. What?

173
00:08:05.719 --> 00:08:07.347
This is precisely
what we do here. sir.

174
00:08:07.420 --> 00:08:10.117
We find people. We'll
find your Brandon.

175
00:08:16.129 --> 00:08:18.291
Okay. make sure
we are not disturbed.

176
00:08:18.365 --> 00:08:21.529
I need five minutes uninterrupted.
Make sure no one comes in.

177
00:08:21.601 --> 00:08:22.660
Yeah.

178
00:08:29.476 --> 00:08:31.741
What's with all the
secrecy. O'Hara?

179
00:08:31.811 --> 00:08:33.439
I've got a real mindbender.

180
00:08:33.513 --> 00:08:35.345
Problem with the railway theft?

181
00:08:35.415 --> 00:08:37.748
No. It's a detective.

182
00:08:37.817 --> 00:08:39.843
Is this something
for Internal Affairs?

183
00:08:39.919 --> 00:08:41.581
It's Detective Lassiter.

184
00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:43.199
What's the problem
with our Head Detective?

185
00:08:43.223 --> 00:08:44.384
Well. it's his birthday.

186
00:08:44.457 --> 00:08:46.358
Oh. that's not a problem.

187
00:08:46.426 --> 00:08:48.827
Yeah! It is! He seems quiet.

188
00:08:48.895 --> 00:08:50.693
He is quiet. That's who he is.

189
00:08:50.764 --> 00:08:52.875
Look. O'Hara. I think it's nice
that you care for your partner.

190
00:08:52.899 --> 00:08:54.993
but he is a grown
man. He'll be fine.

191
00:08:55.068 --> 00:08:57.833
I just thought it would
be nice to surprise him.

192
00:08:57.904 --> 00:08:58.997
Oh...

193
00:08:59.472 --> 00:09:01.634
Detective Lassiter
does not like surprises.

194
00:09:01.708 --> 00:09:03.686
Of course he likes surprises.
Everybody likes surprises.

195
00:09:03.710 --> 00:09:07.203
Detective Lassiter has a
very particular comfort zone.

196
00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:11.149
And you don't even wanna know what we
now call the Secret Santa Debacle of 2005.

197
00:09:11.217 --> 00:09:13.584
I just wanted to do
something nice for him.

198
00:09:13.653 --> 00:09:14.830
but nobody seems
to know what he likes!

199
00:09:14.854 --> 00:09:17.221
Well. you're his partner.
shouldn't you know?

200
00:09:18.858 --> 00:09:20.759
Well. we don't really talk.

201
00:09:21.227 --> 00:09:22.718
I mean. he doesn't.

202
00:09:22.796 --> 00:09:27.461
He nods and responds mostly.
He never really poses a question.

203
00:09:27.534 --> 00:09:31.562
Although sometimes he
asks if we can ride in silence.

204
00:09:31.638 --> 00:09:34.335
O'Hara. your heart
is in the right place.

205
00:09:34.607 --> 00:09:37.441
but I am very sure that you're
gonna have to do this yourself.

206
00:09:37.510 --> 00:09:38.978
Okay. fine.

207
00:09:45.151 --> 00:09:46.642
Shawn. what are we doin' here?

208
00:09:46.719 --> 00:09:48.745
Brandon's dad
said he was evicted.

209
00:09:48.822 --> 00:09:50.688
Gus. let me ask you something.

210
00:09:50.757 --> 00:09:52.968
When's the last time you were
evicted from your apartment?

211
00:09:52.992 --> 00:09:54.153
Never!

212
00:09:56.196 --> 00:09:58.563
Exactly. You
wouldn't understand.

213
00:09:58.631 --> 00:10:00.065
This is my world.

214
00:10:03.803 --> 00:10:06.329
So the landlord keeps
Brandon's stuff as collateral.

215
00:10:06.406 --> 00:10:08.136
Brandon comes back.
the landlord gets paid.

216
00:10:08.208 --> 00:10:10.074
Brandon doesn't.
there's a garage sale.

217
00:10:10.143 --> 00:10:12.044
Well. the buzzer upstairs
says that his is 227.

218
00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:14.343
<i>227?</i> Marla Gibbs. Regina King.

219
00:10:14.414 --> 00:10:15.882
Jackée! Hal Williams.

220
00:10:15.949 --> 00:10:18.145
Hal Williams? Hal
Williams as Lester Jenkins.

221
00:10:18.218 --> 00:10:19.550
Yeah. right.

222
00:10:23.690 --> 00:10:25.955
Looks like somebody took
a screwdriver to this thing.

223
00:10:26.025 --> 00:10:27.254
Lemme see.

224
00:10:28.294 --> 00:10:31.355
Okay. so Brandon needed something
inside here. but he couldn't get in.

225
00:10:31.431 --> 00:10:33.351
If you were in his shoes.
what would you do next?

226
00:10:33.399 --> 00:10:35.300
First of all. I'd feel
very ashamed of myself.

227
00:10:35.368 --> 00:10:36.961
Tell me about it.

228
00:10:45.311 --> 00:10:46.711
But then.

229
00:10:48.815 --> 00:10:50.909
I think I'd come back
with some scissors.

230
00:10:52.452 --> 00:10:54.921
Let's see if we can find
what he's reaching for.

231
00:10:54.988 --> 00:10:56.820
Yeah. lemme reach.
My reach is better.

232
00:10:56.890 --> 00:10:58.085
Excuse me? What?

233
00:10:58.158 --> 00:10:59.878
When exactly did we
have a reaching contest?

234
00:10:59.926 --> 00:11:01.036
My reach has always been better.

235
00:11:01.060 --> 00:11:04.155
But my arms are
slender-erer. Slender-erer?

236
00:11:04.230 --> 00:11:06.995
What? Slendererer...

237
00:11:07.066 --> 00:11:08.466
Skinnier? Yes.

238
00:11:08.535 --> 00:11:12.063
You know what? You're right. My biceps probably
wouldn't fit through this thing anyway.

239
00:11:12.138 --> 00:11:14.198
I knew you'd fall for that!

240
00:11:22.081 --> 00:11:23.674
Let me see.

241
